\import{table-macros}
\title{Old-fashioned Mac Software still unbeaten}
\author{liamoc}
\date{2026-03-08}
\p{Growing increasingly frustrated with the Apple mail client's seemingly unfixable inability to search for emails \em{I just read}, I made the switch to [MailMate](https://freron.com/), a good old-fashioned Mac OS X-style app with a lot of useful features, good performance, and, most importantly, \em{working search}. Of course, ANU in their infinite wisdom have not seen fit to bless MailMate as an allowed client on their OAuth server, but this is nothing that a little [davmail](https://davmail.sourceforge.net/) can't fix... }
\p{In general, the quality of software on the Mac is getting worse, primarily because a large amount of it isn't even \em{for the Mac} (and secondarily because Apple themselves are enshittifying their software and their design guidelines). I'm tired of running 18 instances of Chromium to do basic tasks. This is why I continue to use [Nova](https://nova.app/), [TextMate](https://macromates.com/), MailMate, etc. I would use [Orion](https://orionbrowser.com/) too, except for its jankiness and poor performance compared to [Zen](https://zen-browser.app/). The other major motivation is my aversion to the dreaded bots and those who use them, which is why I moved away from ghostty and to [alacritty](https://alacritty.org/) lately, although I'd welcome suggestions there. }